# behavioral-scoring-algorithms

Core Behavioral Scoring Components:

1. Daily Performance Notes (DPN) System
Importance Score: 95 — This is a priority weight used to rank this component relative to others when resolving conflicts or allocating AI processing resources; it does not factor directly into aggregate behavioral scores. The aggregate score formula is: Aggregate DPN Score = (PeerInteraction + AdultInteraction + InvestmentLevel + AuthorityResponse) / 4, producing a composite 0–4 value used in rolling period calculations.

Four-domain behavioral rating matrix (0–4 scale per domain):

  Peer Interaction:
    0 = Actively aggressive or harmful toward peers; physical or severe verbal altercations
    1 = Frequent negative peer engagement; taunting, exclusion, or persistent conflict
    2 = Inconsistent peer behavior; some positive interactions mixed with minor conflict
    3 = Generally cooperative with peers; minor friction resolved without staff intervention
    4 = Consistently prosocial; actively supports and encourages peers

  Adult Interaction:
    0 = Refuses all adult contact; threatening or physically aggressive toward staff
    1 = Frequent non-compliance; arguing, defiance, or disrespectful language
    2 = Inconsistent compliance; responds to redirection after initial resistance
    3 = Generally respectful; follows direction with minimal prompting
    4 = Proactively respectful; seeks adult guidance appropriately

  Investment Level:
    0 = Refuses participation in all programming; completely disengaged
    1 = Minimal effort; participates only when directly prompted and monitored
    2 = Partial effort; engages inconsistently across activities
    3 = Consistent effort in most programming; occasional disengagement
    4 = Full engagement; demonstrates initiative and intrinsic motivation

  Authority Response:
    0 = Refuses all authority; attempts to circumvent or undermine facility rules
    1 = Persistent rule violations; does not self-correct after consequences
    2 = Accepts consequences but requires repeated reminders of rules
    3 = Follows rules consistently; accepts consequences without escalation
    4 = Internalizes rules; models compliance for peers and self-advocates appropriately

AI-enhanced comment generation: Comments are generated using OpenAI GPT-4o-mini (standard tier) or GPT-4o (premium tier) via the server-side `/api/ai/query` endpoint. The model receives the numeric domain scores and prior session notes as structured context and outputs clinically neutral, trauma-informed prose. Training data is OpenAI's base pretraining corpus; no facility-specific fine-tuning is applied. Validation: staff reviewed a sample of 50 AI-generated comments and rated clinical appropriateness on a 1–5 scale; mean rating 4.1. Bias mitigation: prompts explicitly require neutral language free of demographic assumptions; all generated text is editable by staff before saving. Human review workflow: every AI-generated comment must be reviewed and saved by an authorized staff member (role: direct care staff or above) before it becomes part of the permanent record. There is no automatic write-back; AI output is advisory only. SLA for review: comments must be finalized within the same shift in which they are generated. Appeals: a youth or guardian may request clinical supervisor review of any saved comment within 30 days; the supervisor may amend or annotate the record.

Rolling period calculations:
  Daily: raw aggregate DPN score for the calendar day
  Weekly: arithmetic mean of the last 7 daily scores
  Monthly: arithmetic mean of all daily scores in the calendar month

Threshold-based status indicators (applied to the rolling period composite score):
  Green: composite score >= 3.0 — youth is meeting behavioral expectations
  Yellow: composite score >= 2.0 and < 3.0 — youth requires monitoring and targeted support
  Red: composite score < 2.0 — youth requires immediate clinical review and intervention planning

